Don't just do it, Do it right!

Thanks for the unfiltered feature @businessinsider. Just a little correction that we do not just wash the bags with water, we use a disinfectant. Also the waste collectors do not work in 12 hours shifts they have a 3 hour break from 12 pm to 3 pm as it is too hot and humid to expect any one to work under those conditions. Many of the commentators seemed to be rather perplexed looking at our skilled personnel wearing shoes that weren’t thaelys and thought we haven’t  provided the makers our shoes; everyone that’s part of the process owns a pair but simply choose to wear what they find convenient on a daily basis, we don’t believe in enforcing a change of personal style on our employees! And, the shoes are definitely NOT made for 2$ 😂 would y’all like a more in-depth breakdown of why thaely Y2Ks cost as much as they do? Let us know in the comments!
